Growing up in Dallas in the 90s… I’ve  loved the Cowboys as far back as I can remember. So I’d say Sunday was a dream come true…but this was something I couldn’t even dream of being a possibility. Getting to fly the stadium with Jerry Jones in his helicopter, getting to go on the field and see the players warm up, recording an interview with Jerry beforehand and then watching the game from his suite…it still feels like a dream! Thanks to @dallascowboys for being so awesome to us and this once in a lifetime experience. And to @mrbobbybones always bringing me along to be a part of the cool things.

Happy birthday to my favorite person. She’s everyone’s biggest cheerleader and the best team mate in life. Just when I didn’t think it was possible for me to find love…I realized it was just a matter of time until the perfect person came along. She’s like me in all the ways that compliment me…and different in all the ways I needed to be challenged in life. She’s the most beautiful, smartest, loving person I’ll ever know. I love you @kelsey.rodriguez_ !

finished my 2nd marathon! 26.2 miles in a total time: 3:36:19. (8:12 per mile). The best run of my life! felt great. the last 6 miles proved again to be brutal but couldn't have asked for better running weather. to think how far i've come in my health and fitness journey. i never thought this would be possible. thanks to everyone for the support! thanks to all who donated to support @stjude. and thanks to @kelsey.rodriguez_ for being the best wife and being there to cheer me on!
